<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Festival1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Festival,</orth> subst. a time of public joy, a day kept sacred and celebrated: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.6.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 6, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 29</bibl>. <cit><quote>our solemn f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 103</bibl></cit> (i. e. our marriage-feast). <cit><quote>I cannot woo in f. terms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 2, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>their f. purses,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.627" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 627</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>